  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut the <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with<strong> olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1600174841540-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1600174841540-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1600174841540-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1600174841540-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1600174841540-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, pat the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong> and season them with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned chicken thighs</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 7-8 min or until the skins have browned and crisped</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1600174860036-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1600174860036-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1600174860036-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1600174860036-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1600174860036-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cut into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1600174876384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1600174876384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1600174876384-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1600174876384-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1600174876384-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the<strong> lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut into wedges</p><p>Squeeze the <strong>juice</strong> of the <strong>lemon wedges</strong> into a large bowl (not sure about citrus? Try using less!)</p><p>Add the <strong>juiced wedges</strong> to the bowl</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600174883318-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600174883318-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600174883318-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600174883318-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600174883318-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>crisped chicken thighs</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>courgette</strong> and the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the bowl with the <strong>lemon</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chicken mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600174898065-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600174898065-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600174898065-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600174898065-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600174898065-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had 15 min, add the <strong>chicken mixture</strong> to the baking tray</p><p>Tip: Place the chicken thighs skin-side up for extra crispiness!</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 10 min further</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1600174908863-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
